    {
      "id": "question_37072878002",
      "label": "This role is an individual contributor role (not a managing a team). If you are currently managing a team please share why you'd be open to an IC role? ",
      "type": "textarea",
      "required": true,
      "value": "I'm excited about the opportunity to work at Motive because I'm drawn to organizations that operate at scale, solve complex technical challenges, and prioritize innovation and long-term impact. Throughout my experience at Microsoft and Amazon Robotics, I've enjoyed working at the intersection of technology, operations, and strategy — leading cross-functional initiatives, building scalable systems, and driving measurable business outcomes.\n\nWhat particularly interests me about Motive is the opportunity to contribute to high-impact products and programs while collaborating with talented teams across engineering, product, and business functions. I'm especially motivated by environments where I can combine technical depth with program leadership to improve reliability, automation, and operational efficiency.\n\nIn my current role, I've led large-scale resilience and automation initiatives, developed AI-driven workflow solutions, and managed complex cross-organizational programs under executive visibility. I enjoy taking ambiguous problems, creating structure, and driving execution from concept through delivery. I'd be excited to bring that same mindset to Motive while continuing to grow in a fast-paced and innovative environment.\n\nBeyond the technical challenges, I'm also looking for a company whose culture emphasizes ownership, collaboration, and continuous improvement. From what I've seen, Motive aligns strongly with those values, which makes the opportunity especially compelling to me.",
      "source": "why-company-template.md (substituted [Company]='Motive')",
      "status": "filled",
      "matched_rule": "why_company_essay",
      "options": null
    },
